properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 8 at 3:29PM AKST until February 9 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions. Additional snow accumulations of up
to 12 inches. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph.

* WHERE...Thompson Pass.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit 511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST SUNDAY THROUGH THOMPSON PASS
